An '''aviation ministry''' is a [[Cabinet (government)|cabinet level]] department of a [[government]] which is concerned with matters of [[aviation]] within a particular country's [[airspace]]. An aviation ministry may also be involved with a nation's [[air force]], either to a limited degree or in direct command.

One of the more well known aviation ministries was the [[Ministry of Aviation (Germany)|aviation ministry]] of [[Nazi Germany]] which formed the [[Luftwaffe]] under [[Hermann GÃ¶ring]]. Other nations, for instance the [[United States]], do not have a cabinet or state level department for aviation, but rather civilian or federally sponsored civilian agencies, one of the better known being the [[Federal Aviation Administration]].

